A comment on this photo just came to us via email, from David, a non-Flickr user who wrote: 

&quot;...On the discussion about the photo of the original Sydney Terminal Station someone asked “who wrote ‘Redfern NSW’ on the Powerhouse’s print?”  The answer is that Redfern WAS the original Sydney Terminal Station and when it was demolished to make way for what is now Central the name Redfern was transferred to Eveleigh station (since noone remembers who he was but Dr Redfern was famous).  That is why the Locomotive and Carriage Works on the east and west, respectively, of the line at Redfern still bear the name Eveleigh Workshops (or did when I worked there).&quot;

AB
